714175f-a.title: Manhattan: 64th Street - Amsterdam Avenue
714175f-a.text:
64th Street, north side, west from 227 West 64th, between Amsterdam and West End avenues. The building in the foreground, 229E43, is the Warren-Nash Motor Corporation, (service station and
ganeral offices).
bout 1900.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

714174f-a.title: Manhattan: 64th Street (West) - Amsterdam Avenue
714174f-a.text:
211 West 64th Street, north side, west of Amsterdam Avenue. This is a two-story frame building with a stone front.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York
Negative No. 504

714172f-a.title: Manhattan: 64th Street (West) - Amsterdam Avenue
714172f-a.text:
West. 64th Street, at, adjoining and east of the N. E. corner of Amsterdam Avenue (left), showing a garage at No. 167, and the Centro Galacia at No. 153-59. The latter replaced the brownstones that housed the Society of Professional Auto Engineers in 1922. View 2 shows the roof atop the garage that adjoins this building. The photographer is viewing northwestward towards Amsterdam Avenue from a
point in the center of the block.
July 6, 1937
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
